 de·bauch·er·y    Pronunciation Key  (d-bôch-r)
n. pl. de·bauch·er·ies

   1.
         1. Extreme indulgence in sensual pleasures; dissipation.
         2. debaucheries Orgies.
   2. Archaic. Seduction from morality, allegiance, or duty.

debauchery

